manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: MOUNTUP Tilting TV Wall Mount MOUNTUP TILTING TV WALL MOUNT FOR 37" - 75" TVS Set up your TVs at a perfect viewing angle with this universal tilt TV mount MU0008. The wall mount TV bracket is designed for most 37-75 inches LCD, LED, or Plasma screens and the max weight of 99 lbs TVs, the VESA patterns from 150x100mm to 600x400mm, and the wood studs spacing up to 24 inches.

How to choose a suitable TV mount? Step 1: Check Wall Types The TV mount MU0008 is designed for wood studs spacing of 16/18/24 inches.It also can be mounted on concrete or brick walls. Concrete anchors are not included, they will be sent if needed. ( Note： Not for dry wall alone application.) Step 2: Check VESA Pattern VESA=HorizontalxVertical (mm) (The 4 mount holes on TV back)Make sure your TV's VESA pattern is between 150x100mm and 600x400mm.Accommodate VESA patterns: 150x100, 200x100, 200x200, 200x300, 300x200, 300x300, 400x200, 400x300, 400x400, 500x300, 600x400. Step 3: Check TV Specs Confirm your TV's weight is less than 99 lbs.Confirm your TV's size is between 37 and 75 inches. The tv wall mount is compatible with including but not limited to 37, 39, 40, 42, 43, 49, 50, 55, 60, 65, 70, 75 inches TVs.

Why choose this Tilting TV Wall Mount? 1. Heavy-Duty Steel Construction Low profile TV wall mount features heavy-duty cold-formed steel construction. It has been strength tested to ensure security for your TV and your family. 2. Low Profile Design The wall mount TV bracket extends only 1.67 inches from the wall for a sleek appearance to save space. 3. 10° Tilt Adjustment Easily tilt the TV down 10° to reduce glare for comfortable viewing to enjoy any TV show or movie. 4. Unique Quick Release Design The locking system with a quick-release design allows the TV to remove and adjust easily. PACKING LIST: 1 x TV mount, 1 x bubble level, 3 x velcro cable ties, 1x user manual, all standard mounting hardware. NOTE: Concrete anchors are not included, they will be sent if needed. DO NOT MOUNT ON DRYWALL ALONE!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 25, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Best TV mount
reviews.reviewText: We upsized on our flat screen and needed a mount that could carry the load. This one is perfect. Easy to install. Comes with spacers ( turned out we needed them ) and all the hardware you need. Even comes with a handy dandy little wrench but my construction foreman husband used his Dewalt, lol. Over kill much!!! I think so! Any hoo..........I definitely recommend this mount. Great price and shipped quickly. Material is sturdy, not flimsy like some brackets can me. Nice black finish. Pull cords make for easy and quick release. Go get you one!!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 14, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Simple, reasonable, basic, could purchase
reviews.reviewText: Better than expected if you need a simple reasonable basic Mount. Doesn't take up much room. Just simple wall mount. Pro is it gets the TV as close as possible to the wall. Con not much room to manipulate wires. I would recommend this for more of a simple bedroom TV without a bunch of cables. Living room TVs you need to have a little bit more room and maneuverability but works amazing for bedroom clean look basic mounts in my opinion anyway.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 16, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Easy to install and sturdy
reviews.reviewText: Bought 2 of these. 1 for 65" and 1 for 55" tv.Both installed easily but had to add some spacers to wallount to allow more space between tv back and wall, and allow a better tilt down angle. But after mounting, both tvs look great and support tv well.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 9, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Nice, easy, and sturdy!
reviews.reviewText: Have this holding up a 55" Hisense U6H. Found the studs with a stud finder, threw up the mount, and presto, mounted TV! Whole installation took probably 30 minutes and transformed the look of our living room! Used some cable raceways to hide the cables from the TV to the media center (not gonna run cables through the wall in an apartment) and it looks like a professional did it!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 4, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Good mount for the price
reviews.reviewText: Worked well for our 55" flat screen.Easy to install. Included all the hardware needed for any variable we had for mount compatibility.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 27, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Good solid mount but some issues
reviews.reviewText: Like it being a solid mount but the bracket could be longer because my location to mount in the middle of the wall did not let me hit all but 1 stud in the center of the bracket and my studs are 16" center. So the 2 on the outside part of the bracket I had to use bolts that are made for hollow walls. My opinion not as strong as studs. Otherwise it's a very close mount to the wall. Make sure you lengthen the quick release rope to be able to unmount the tv or let the TV come away from the wall so you can get to your inputs and such on the back of your TV.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 16, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Worth the buy!
reviews.reviewText: This was one super easy installation. Everything well packaged. Even has a mini level. Lol Bolts and screws galore had plenty of extras and they were compartmentalized. Came with directions but other than a quick glance were not needed. Price was great too! The man didn't even cuss once putting it up LOL
